Privacy Policy for EthnoHealer

Last Updated: February 15, 2026

EthnoHealer (“we”, “our”, “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it through this Privacy Policy. This policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use the EthnoHealer mobile application and related services (the “App”), built for the Pi Network ecosystem.

By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

1. About EthnoHealer

EthnoHealer is a Pi Network application designed to connect users with traditional healing knowledge, cultural wellness resources, and community-based health information.

2. Information We Collect

We collect only the minimum information required to operate and improve the App.

2.1 Information You Provide

When using the App, we may collect:

Pi Network username and user ID

Profile information you voluntarily provide (nickname, bio, preferences)

Messages, feedback, or inquiries sent to us

Content you submit within the app (posts, comments, healing tips)

2.2 Automatically Collected Information

We may automatically collect:

Device type and operating system

App usage data and interaction logs

IP address and approximate location (for security and analytics)

Error and crash reports

2.3 Pi Network Data

EthnoHealer integrates with Pi Network authentication. We do not access passwords or private keys. We only receive basic account information provided by Pi Network for authentication.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use collected information to:

Provide and maintain the App

Authenticate users via Pi Network

Enable community features and interactions

Improve app performance and user experience

Prevent fraud, abuse, or illegal activity

Respond to user inquiries and support requests

Comply with legal obligations

We do not sell your personal data.

4. How We Share Information

We may share information only in limited circumstances:

4.1 Service Providers

We may share data with trusted service providers who help us operate the App (hosting, analytics, security). They are contractually obligated to protect your data.

4.2 Legal Requirements

We may disclose information if required by law, regulation, or legal process.

4.3 Business Transfers

If EthnoHealer is merged, acquired, or sold, user data may be transferred as part of the business assets.

5. Data Storage and Security

We implement industry-standard safeguards including:

Secure servers and encrypted connections (HTTPS)

Access controls and authentication measures

Regular security monitoring

However, no digital system is completely secure. Users share information at their own risk.

6. Data Retention

We retain personal data only as long as necessary to:

Provide services

Comply with legal obligations

Resolve disputes

Enforce agreements

You may request deletion of your data at any time.

7. Children’s Privacy

EthnoHealer is not intended for children under 13.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn that a child has provided data, we will delete it promptly.

8. Your Privacy Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

Access your personal data

Correct inaccurate information

Request deletion of your data

Object to data processing

Withdraw consent

To exercise your rights, contact us using the details below.

9. Third-Party Links and Content

The App may contain links to third-party websites or services.
We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Please review their policies separately.

10. International Users

Your information may be stored or processed in countries outside your own. By using the App, you consent to cross-border data transfers.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
Updates will be posted in the App with a revised “Last Updated” date.

Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated policy.

12. Contact Us

If you have questions or privacy requests, contact:

EthnoHealer Support Team
Email: support@ethnohealer.app
